.\" zenctl.1 - manual page for the zenctl CLI
.\"
.\" groff_man(7) source. View with: man -l man/zenctl.1
.TH ZENCTL 1 "2026-07-11" "zenctl 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
zenctl \- hardware control for Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SY zenctl
.OP domain subcommand
.OP target
.OP options
.YS
.SY zenctl
.BR profile " " \fBsave\fR|\fBload\fR|\fBlist\fR|\fBdelete\fR " " \fIname\fR
.YS
.SY zenctl
.B caps
.RI [ domain ]
.YS
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B zenctl
is a thin command-line wrapper around
.BR libzenctl (3).
It reads and writes hardware controls exposed by the Linux kernel
through sysfs, procfs, ioctl, and ACPI/WMI. Every hardware operation
the CLI performs is a call into the library; no sysfs path, ioctl, or
EFI variable is touched directly by the binary.
.PP
The CLI does argument parsing, output formatting (human-readable table
or JSON), and privilege checks. Writes require root. Destructive writes
require an explicit
.B \-\-confirm
flag or an interactive prompt.
.B \-\-dry\-run
is available on every write subcommand.
.PP
Domains: cpu, mem, storage, net, pcie, gpu, thermal, power, usb, bt,
wireless, firmware. The
.B profile
and
.B caps
verbs sit outside the domain/subcommand pattern.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS "cpu \- CPU controls"
.TP
.B zenctl cpu get governor \-\-cpu N
Print the active cpufreq governor for CPU N.
.TP
.BI "zenctl cpu set governor " "NAME \-\-cpu N|all"
Set the cpufreq governor (e.g. performance, powersave, schedutil).
.TP
.B zenctl cpu get freq \-\-cpu N
Print the minimum and maximum scaling frequency in Hz.
.TP
.BI "zenctl cpu set freq\-min " "HZ \-\-cpu N|all"
Set the minimum scaling frequency. HZ accepts Hz, MHz, or GHz
(see FREQUENCY UNITS below).
.TP
.BI "zenctl cpu set freq\-max " "HZ \-\-cpu N|all"
Set the maximum scaling frequency. HZ accepts Hz, MHz, or GHz
(see FREQUENCY UNITS below).
.TP
.B zenctl cpu get online \-\-cpu N
Print whether CPU N is online.
.TP
.BI "zenctl cpu set online " "on|off \-\-cpu N"
Bring CPU N online or take it offline. Destructive; requires
.BR \-\-confirm .
.TP
.B zenctl cpu get smt
Print whether SMT is active.
.TP
.BI "zenctl cpu set smt " "on|off"
Enable or disable SMT. Destructive; requires
.BR \-\-confirm .
.TP
.BI "zenctl cpu get cstate " "\-\-cpu N \-\-state N"
Print C-state disable flags for CPU N. Without
.B \-\-state
every C-state is listed.
.TP
.BI "zenctl cpu set cstate " "STATE enable|disable \-\-cpu N"
Enable or disable C-state STATE on CPU N.
.SS "mem \- memory, hugepages, NUMA, VM tunables"
.TP
.B zenctl mem get hugepages
Print the number of default-size hugepages reserved and the hugepage size.
.TP
.BI "zenctl mem set hugepages " N
Set the number of default-size hugepages.
.TP
.B zenctl mem get thp
Print the transparent huge pages mode (always, madvise, never).
.TP
.BI "zenctl mem set thp " "always|madvise|never"
Set the THP mode.
.TP
.B zenctl mem get numa
Print the NUMA node count plus per-node memory totals and CPU mask.
.TP
.B zenctl mem get swappiness
Print /proc/sys/vm/swappiness.
.TP
.BI "zenctl mem set swappiness " "0..200"
Set vm.swappiness.
.TP
.B zenctl mem get overcommit
Print /proc/sys/vm/overcommit_memory.
.TP
.BI "zenctl mem set overcommit " "0|1|2"
Set vm.overcommit_memory (0 = heuristic, 1 = always, 2 = never).
.SS "storage \- block device controls"
.TP
.B zenctl storage list
List every block device under /sys/block.
.TP
.BI "zenctl storage get scheduler " "\-\-dev DEV"
Print the active I/O scheduler for DEV plus the available schedulers.
.TP
.BI "zenctl storage set scheduler " "NAME \-\-dev DEV"
Set the I/O scheduler (e.g. mq-deadline, bfq, none, kyber).
.TP
.BI "zenctl storage get queue\-depth " "\-\-dev DEV"
Print the hardware queue depth.
.TP
.BI "zenctl storage get read\-ahead " "\-\-dev DEV"
Print read-ahead in kB.
.TP
.BI "zenctl storage set read\-ahead " "KB \-\-dev DEV"
Set read-ahead in kB.
.TP
.BI "zenctl storage get cache\-type " "\-\-dev DEV"
Print the write cache mode.
.TP
.BI "zenctl storage set cache\-type " "TYPE \-\-dev DEV"
Set the write cache mode (write_back, write_through, none).
.TP
.BI "zenctl storage get stats " "\-\-dev DEV"
Print the I/O stats line from /sys/block/<dev>/stat.
.TP
.BI "zenctl storage get power " "\-\-dev DEV"
Print the runtime PM mode (on, auto).
.TP
.BI "zenctl storage set power " "auto|on \-\-dev DEV"
Set the runtime PM mode.
.SS "net \- NIC controls"
.TP
.B zenctl net list
List every interface under /sys/class/net.
.TP
.BI "zenctl net get ring " "\-\-iface IFACE"
Print the RX and TX ring sizes and their hardware maxima.
.TP
.BI "zenctl net set ring " "rx|tx N \-\-iface IFACE"
Set the RX or TX ring size.
.TP
.BI "zenctl net get offload " "\-\-iface IFACE"
Print the TSO, GRO, GSO, RXCSUM, and TXCSUM offload flags.
.TP
.BI "zenctl net set offload " "tso|gro|gso|rxcsum|txcsum on|off \-\-iface IFACE"
Set one offload flag.
.TP
.BI "zenctl net get link " "\-\-iface IFACE"
Print link state, speed in Mbps, and duplex mode.
.TP
.BI "zenctl net get mtu " "\-\-iface IFACE"
Print the MTU.
.TP
.BI "zenctl net set mtu " "N \-\-iface IFACE"
Set the MTU (68..65536).
.TP
.BI "zenctl net get irq " "\-\-iface IFACE"
Print the IRQ number and smp_affinity cpumask.
.TP
.BI "zenctl net set irq\-affinity " "MASK \-\-iface IFACE"
Set the IRQ smp_affinity cpumask (hex).
.SS "pcie \- PCIe link, power, ASPM, IOMMU, NUMA"
.TP
.B zenctl pcie list
List every PCI device under /sys/bus/pci/devices.
.TP
.BI "zenctl pcie get link " "\-\-addr ADDR"
Print current and maximum link speed and width.
.TP
.BI "zenctl pcie get power " "\-\-addr ADDR"
Print the device runtime PM mode and D3cold-allowed flag.
.TP
.BI "zenctl pcie set power " "auto|on \-\-addr ADDR"
Set the device runtime PM mode.
.TP
.BI "zenctl pcie get iommu " "\-\-addr ADDR"
Print the IOMMU group ID for the device.
.TP
.BI "zenctl pcie get numa " "\-\-addr ADDR"
Print the NUMA node for the device (-1 if unknown).
.TP
.BI "zenctl pcie get info " "\-\-addr ADDR"
Print the PCI vendor ID, device ID, and class code.
.TP
.B zenctl pcie get aspm
Print the global ASPM policy.
.SS "gpu \- GPU controls"
.TP
.B zenctl gpu list
List every DRM card under /sys/class/drm.
.TP
.BI "zenctl gpu get temp " "\-\-card N"
Print the GPU temperature in millidegrees Celsius.
.TP
.BI "zenctl gpu get fan " "\-\-card N"
Print the fan PWM value and auto-control flag.
.TP
.BI "zenctl gpu set fan " "N|auto \-\-card N"
Set the fan PWM (0-255) or enable auto control.
.TP
.BI "zenctl gpu get power " "\-\-card N"
Print the current power draw in microwatts.
.TP
.BI "zenctl gpu get freq " "\-\-card N"
Print the current GPU clock in MHz.
.TP
.BI "zenctl gpu get driver " "\-\-card N"
Print the DRM driver name.
.TP
.BI "zenctl gpu get profile " "\-\-card N"
Print the AMDGPU power profile.
.TP
.BI "zenctl gpu set profile " "NAME \-\-card N"
Set the AMDGPU power profile.
.TP
.BI "zenctl gpu get busy " "\-\-card N"
Print the AMDGPU busy percentage.
.TP
.B zenctl gpu get \-\-all \-\-card N
Print every readable attribute of every card, or the one selected by
.BR \-\-card .
.SS "thermal \- thermal zones, cooling devices, hwmon"
.TP
.B zenctl thermal list
List every thermal zone.
.TP
.BI "zenctl thermal get temp " "\-\-zone Z"
Print the zone temperature in millidegrees Celsius.
.TP
.BI "zenctl thermal get type " "\-\-zone Z"
Print the zone type string.
.TP
.BI "zenctl thermal get policy " "\-\-zone Z"
Print the active thermal governor.
.TP
.BI "zenctl thermal set policy " "NAME \-\-zone Z"
Set the thermal governor.
.TP
.BI "zenctl thermal get mode " "\-\-zone Z"
Print whether the zone is enabled.
.TP
.BI "zenctl thermal set mode " "enabled|disabled \-\-zone Z"
Enable or disable the zone.
.TP
.BI "zenctl thermal get trips " "\-\-zone Z"
Print every trip point (index, type, temp, hysteresis).
.TP
.BI "zenctl thermal get cooling " "\-\-zone Z"
Print every cooling device bound to Z (type, cur_state, max_state).
.TP
.BI "zenctl thermal set cooling " "INDEX STATE \-\-zone Z"
Set the cur_state of cooling device INDEX.
.TP
.B zenctl thermal hwmon
List every hwmon sensor.
.TP
.BI "zenctl thermal hwmon fan " "HWMON FAN [N]"
Get (no N) or set (N in 0..255) a hwmon fan PWM value.
.SS "power \- sleep states, battery, AC, wake sources"
.TP
.B zenctl power get states
Print the supported ACPI sleep states.
.TP
.BI "zenctl power suspend " "freeze|mem|disk|standby \-\-confirm"
Enter the given sleep state. Destructive; requires
.BR \-\-confirm .
.TP
.B zenctl power get mem\-sleep
Print the mem_sleep mode (s2idle, shallow, deep).
.TP
.BI "zenctl power set mem\-sleep " MODE
Set the mem_sleep mode.
.TP
.BI "zenctl power get battery " "[N]"
Print battery N status and capacity, or every battery when N is omitted.
.TP
.BI "zenctl power get charge\-thresholds " N
Print the charge start and end thresholds for battery N.
.TP
.BI "zenctl power set charge\-start " "N PERCENT"
Set the charge-start threshold for battery N.
.TP
.BI "zenctl power set charge\-end " "N PERCENT"
Set the charge-end threshold for battery N.
.TP
.B zenctl power get ac
Print whether the AC adapter is online.
.TP
.B zenctl power get wakeup
Print the list of configured wakeup devices.
.SS "usb \- USB devices"
.TP
.B zenctl usb list
List every USB device under /sys/bus/usb/devices.
.TP
.BI "zenctl usb get " "power|autosuspend|authorized|wakeup DEV"
Print one USB device attribute.
.TP
.BI "zenctl usb set power " "auto|on DEV"
Set the runtime PM mode.
.TP
.BI "zenctl usb set autosuspend " "DEV MS"
Set the autosuspend delay in milliseconds.
.TP
.BI "zenctl usb set authorized " "DEV on|off"
Authorize or deauthorize a device. Deauthorizing requires
.BR \-\-confirm .
.TP
.BI "zenctl usb set wakeup " "DEV on|off"
Enable or disable remote wakeup.
.TP
.BI "zenctl usb reset " DEV
Reset the device via USBDEVFS_RESET.
.SS "bt \- Bluetooth adapters"
.TP
.B zenctl bt list
List every adapter under /sys/class/bluetooth.
.TP
.BI "zenctl bt get " "power|address ADAPTER"
Print the adapter power state or BD_ADDR.
.TP
.BI "zenctl bt set power " "ADAPTER on|off"
Power the adapter on or off (via rfkill soft-block).
.SS "wireless \- Wi-Fi / cfg80211"
.TP
.B zenctl wireless list
List every phy under /sys/class/ieee80211.
.TP
.BI "zenctl wireless get " "power|regdomain PHY"
Print the PHY power state or regulatory domain.
.TP
.BI "zenctl wireless set power " "PHY on|off"
Power the PHY on or off (via rfkill soft-block).
.SS "firmware \- DMI, EFI, ACPI, BIOS settings"
.TP
.BI "zenctl firmware dmi " FIELD
Print a /sys/class/dmi/id/ FIELD (e.g. bios_vendor, sys_vendor, product_name).
.TP
.B zenctl firmware dmi \-\-all
Print every known DMI field.
.TP
.B zenctl firmware efi list
List every EFI variable in /sys/firmware/efi/efivars/.
.TP
.BI "zenctl firmware efi get " "NAME GUID"
Print the payload of an EFI variable.
.TP
.BI "zenctl firmware efi set " "NAME GUID FILE"
Write or create an EFI variable from FILE. Requires root.
.TP
.BI "zenctl firmware efi delete " "NAME GUID"
Delete an EFI variable. Destructive; requires
.BR \-\-confirm .
.TP
.B zenctl firmware acpi list
List every ACPI table signature present.
.TP
.BI "zenctl firmware acpi get " NAME
Print the raw bytes of ACPI table NAME (DSDT, SSDT, FACP, ...).
.TP
.B zenctl firmware bios list
List every firmware-attributes BIOS setting.
.TP
.BI "zenctl firmware bios get " SETTING
Print one BIOS setting (name, type, current_value, default_value).
.TP
.BI "zenctl firmware bios set " "SETTING VALUE [\-\-password PW]"
Write a new value to a BIOS setting. Requires root.
.SS "profile \- save and restore hardware state"
.TP
.BI "zenctl profile save " NAME
Snapshot the current live state of every available domain to a TOML
profile. v1 covers CPU (governor, freq min/max), memory (swappiness,
THP), and per-device storage (scheduler, read-ahead). Other domains
are skipped.
.TP
.BI "zenctl profile load " NAME
Restore a profile. Respects
.B \-\-dry\-run
and
.BR \-\-confirm .
.TP
.B zenctl profile list
List every saved profile, system and user.
.TP
.BI "zenctl profile delete " NAME
Delete a profile.
.SS "caps \- capability query"
.TP
.BI "zenctl caps " [domain]
Print, for every domain (or every key in
.IR domain
when given), whether the capability is
.BR available ,
.BR readonly ,
or
.BR unavailable .
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-json
Emit machine-parseable JSON. The output always has a
.I "status"
field set to
.I "ok"
or
.IR "error" ,
and either a
.I "data"
field (on success) or an
.I "error"
field (on failure).
.TP
.BR \-\-dry\-run
For any write subcommand: print the planned changes and exit 0 without
touching hardware. Available everywhere, including
.BR "profile load" .
.TP
.BR \-\-confirm
Skip the interactive Y/N prompt for destructive writes. Required (or
the prompt must be answered) for operations like disabling CPU cores,
disabling SMT, entering a sleep state, deleting EFI variables, and
deauthorizing USB devices.
.TP
.BR \-\-help ,\ \ -h
Print usage and exit 0.
.TP
.BR \-\-version ,\ \ -V
Print the
.B zenctl
and
.B libzenctl
versions and exit 0.
.SH SAFETY
.SS "Reads"
Reads run immediately without a prompt. They require root only where
the underlying sysfs file or ioctl does.
.SS "Writes"
Low-risk writes (governor, scheduler, ring size, fan PWM, etc.)
execute after a one-line confirmation to stderr.
.PP
Destructive or irreversible writes require either
.B \-\-confirm
or an interactive Y/N prompt. Destructive operations include:
.IP \(bu 3
disabling CPU cores or SMT
.IP \(bu 3
entering an ACPI sleep state
.IP \(bu 3
deleting EFI variables
.IP \(bu 3
deauthorizing USB devices
.SS "Dry run"
.B \-\-dry\-run
works on every write subcommand and on
.BR "profile load" .
It prints the planned changes and the value they would be set to, then
returns 0. Nothing is written to hardware.
.SS "Privilege"
.B zenctl
is not installed setuid. Call it with
.B sudo
or as root. Every write logs to syslog at the
.B LOG_AUTH
facility with the caller uid, the command, and the values written.
.SH PROFILES
A profile is a named snapshot of hardware state stored as TOML.
.PP
System profiles live in
.IR /etc/zenctl/profiles/ ,
user profiles in
.IR ~/.config/zenctl/profiles/ .
On save the system path is used when running as root, else the user
path. On load the user path is tried first, then the system path.
.PP
Profile format (abbreviated):
.PP
.in +4
.EX
schema_version = 1
profile_name   = "server-perf"

[cpu]
governor = "performance"

[storage."sda"]
scheduler = "mq-deadline"
read_ahead_kb = 256
.EE
.in
.PP
Profiles are versioned via the
.I schema_version
field for forward compatibility. Partial profiles are valid; a profile
need not cover every domain.
.PP
.B zenctl profile save NAME
captures current live state for every domain the library reports as
.BR available .
.B zenctl profile load NAME
replays the profile, applying the same
.B \-\-dry\-run
and
.B \-\-confirm
rules as direct writes.
.SH "FREQUENCY UNITS"
Frequency arguments to
.B "cpu set freq\-min"
and
.B "cpu set freq\-max"
accept plain Hz or a unit suffix:
.RS
.IP \(bu 3
.I 3600000
- plain Hz
.IP \(bu 3
.I 3600MHz
or
.I 3600M
- megahertz
.IP \(bu 3
.I 3.6GHz
or
.I 3.6G
- gigahertz
.IP \(bu 3
.I 3600kHz
or
.I 3600K
- kilohertz
.RE
.IP
Trailing "Hz" after a unit (e.g.
.IR 3.6GHz )
is tolerated. Internally every value is converted to Hz.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Read the active governor on CPU 0:
.PP
.in +4
.EX
zenctl cpu get governor --cpu 0
.EE
.in
.PP
Read the temperature of thermal_zone0:
.PP
.in +4
.EX
zenctl thermal get temp --zone thermal_zone0
.EE
.in
.PP
Read the RX and TX ring sizes on eth0:
.PP
.in +4
.EX
zenctl net get ring --iface eth0
.EE
.in
.PP
Set every CPU to the performance governor (requires root):
.PP
.in +4
.EX
sudo zenctl cpu set governor performance --cpu all
.EE
.in
.PP
Switch sda to the mq-deadline scheduler:
.PP
.in +4
.EX
sudo zenctl storage set scheduler mq-deadline --dev sda
.EE
.in
.PP
Set the GPU fan PWM on card0 to 128:
.PP
.in +4
.EX
sudo zenctl gpu set fan 128 --card 0
.EE
.in
.PP
Dry-run a max-frequency change across all CPUs (writes nothing):
.PP
.in +4
.EX
zenctl cpu set freq-max 3.6GHz --cpu all --dry-run
.EE
.in
.PP
Dump every CPU capability as JSON:
.PP
.in +4
.EX
zenctl caps cpu --json
.EE
.in
.PP
Save and reload a profile:
.PP
.in +4
.EX
sudo zenctl profile save server-perf
sudo zenctl profile load server-perf
.EE
.in
.PP
List profiles as JSON:
.PP
.in +4
.EX
zenctl profile list --json
.EE
.in
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/zenctl/profiles/
System profiles, written by root.
.TP
.I ~/.config/zenctl/profiles/
User profiles.
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/zenctl
The CLI binary.
.TP
.I /usr/local/lib/libzenctl.so*
The shared library the binary links against.
